gov.nasa.arc.brahms.vm.api.events
Interface IGestureActivityInterruptedEM

All Superinterfaces:
IActivityEventConstants, IEventMessage, IGestureEventConstants, java.io.Serializable
public interface IGestureActivityInterruptedEM
extends IEventMessage, IGestureEventConstants

The IGestureActivityInterruptedEM event message is send to the event notifier for every gesture activity that was active but is interrupted by another activity in a workframe with a higher priority.

The contents of this event (property name - type):

  • IGestureActivityInterruptedEM.ACTIVITYCTX - a GestureActivityCtx (object property)
  • IGestureActivityInterruptedEM.STATECTX - an ActivityStateCtx (object property)
  • IGestureActivityInterruptedEM.EVENTTIME - the time of the event (long property)
  • IGestureActivityInterruptedEM.GESTURE - the gesture made in the activity (String property)

Version:
10 April 2002
Author:
Ron van Hoof
